1
00:00:04,938 --> 00:00:07,807
I want you to get rid of that family.

2
00:00:08,975 --> 00:00:12,012
What do you mean "get rid of"?

3
00:00:12,579 --> 00:00:13,980
<i>The Tagusari family…</i>

4
00:00:14,748 --> 00:00:16,216
<i>Kill them all for me.</i>

5
00:00:19,185 --> 00:00:22,822
<i>Mogi regretted it the entire time.</i>

6
00:00:23,623 --> 00:00:26,092
If only back then, I had stopped him…

7
00:00:26,159 --> 00:00:27,027
That's enough.

8
00:00:27,594 --> 00:00:29,596
Wait, I'm still talking--

9
00:00:29,662 --> 00:00:31,531
I've waited 31 years.

10
00:00:31,598 --> 00:00:33,199
That's more than enough.

11
00:00:41,174 --> 00:00:42,375
Makoto.

12
00:00:43,343 --> 00:00:44,677
Let me kill him.

13
00:00:47,414 --> 00:00:48,982
They didn't run away!

14
00:00:50,850 --> 00:00:52,285
They didn't even move.

15
00:00:53,787 --> 00:00:55,355
Sakutaro and Yuka…

16
00:00:55,422 --> 00:00:57,090
They didn't even make a sound.

17
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:00,860
That's what Mogi said.

18
00:01:06,099 --> 00:01:08,501
What are you talking about?
Don't mess with us!

19
00:01:10,370 --> 00:01:11,638
Could it be…

20
00:01:14,741 --> 00:01:16,209
They were already dead?

21
00:01:18,344 --> 00:01:19,946
You too? What are you going on about?

22
00:01:24,551 --> 00:01:25,552
Minoru!

23
00:01:44,304 --> 00:01:45,438
Why did you stop?

24
00:01:48,007 --> 00:01:49,742
She's obviously just bullshitting!

25
00:01:51,077 --> 00:01:53,046
It's true there's no proof.

26
00:01:53,746 --> 00:01:56,850
But there's no proof our parents
were alive back then, either.

27
00:01:57,450 --> 00:01:59,419
You're really going to believe that story?

28
00:02:00,153 --> 00:02:02,255
You can't get revenge
based on speculation.

29
00:02:02,322 --> 00:02:04,090
Mogi is the killer!

30
00:02:04,157 --> 00:02:05,158
But…

31
00:02:05,225 --> 00:02:07,827
If the story is true,
there's a new culprit out there.

32
00:02:10,096 --> 00:02:11,131
Minoru.

33
00:02:11,197 --> 00:02:13,800
That would mean Mogi isn't the killer.

34
00:02:14,701 --> 00:02:17,036
So I have to look into it.

35
00:02:37,056 --> 00:02:40,093
<i>Just what on earth are you hiding?</i>

36
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:43,196
<i>Haruko Ashikaga.</i>

37
00:02:58,111 --> 00:03:00,313
I'll go check
the remaining people involved.

38
00:03:03,249 --> 00:03:07,220
The ones who ordered Mogi to murder them
were the factory manager and Sasaoka.

39
00:03:08,288 --> 00:03:11,224
Amagi from the Igarashi-gumi
might be involved too.

40
00:03:11,724 --> 00:03:13,459
And also Mr. Koike.

41
00:03:35,481 --> 00:03:37,050
I brought food.

42
00:03:37,550 --> 00:03:39,252
If there's anything else you need…

43
00:03:45,825 --> 00:03:47,594
The Tagusaris came, didn't they?

44
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:55,702
My husband committed a crime for my sake.

45
00:04:01,307 --> 00:04:02,742
This time, I thought…

46
00:04:03,843 --> 00:04:06,212
I would be the one to protect my husband.

47
00:04:10,883 --> 00:04:12,819
But I went about it all wrong.

48
00:04:16,189 --> 00:04:17,056
Ms. Karashima.

49
00:04:22,362 --> 00:04:24,464
I don't plan to run away anymore.

50
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:29,202
When those boys come back,

51
00:04:31,504 --> 00:04:34,440
I intend to accept everything.

52
00:04:46,386 --> 00:04:47,320
How did it go?

53
00:04:47,387 --> 00:04:50,456
-What are you doing in your time off?
-Just give your report.

54
00:04:51,357 --> 00:04:53,493
I asked a senior in Anti-Organized Crime.

55
00:04:55,828 --> 00:04:59,432
It seems Amagi from the Igarashi-gumi
died quite a while ago.

56
00:05:00,867 --> 00:05:01,834
He's dead?

57
00:05:02,402 --> 00:05:05,338
Drugs, apparently.
I heard his death was miserable.

58
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,174
By the way…

59
00:05:13,279 --> 00:05:15,148
Why're you looking into this?

60
00:05:17,483 --> 00:05:20,420
<i>The guns were being</i>
<i>traded offshore, weren't they?</i>

61
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:21,888
<i>But that day,</i>

62
00:05:22,355 --> 00:05:24,724
<i>because Sakutaro took a gun home with him…</i>

63
00:05:25,224 --> 00:05:28,094
That fisherman named Koji,

64
00:05:28,161 --> 00:05:30,063
<i>was killed.</i>

65
00:05:31,864 --> 00:05:35,335
Next, look into a Koji who used
to be a fisherman at Yomogida Port.

66
00:05:35,401 --> 00:05:37,637
-Koji?
-I don't know his last name.

67
00:05:37,704 --> 00:05:39,972
But he supposedly died 31 years ago.

68
00:05:41,674 --> 00:05:42,875
Hey, wait.

69
00:05:42,942 --> 00:05:44,477
I'm busy right now!

70
00:05:48,381 --> 00:05:49,315
Only 2,000 yen?

71
00:05:54,854 --> 00:05:56,022
Dr. Kagura.

72
00:05:56,089 --> 00:05:57,523
Do you have a moment?

73
00:05:57,590 --> 00:05:58,725
What's the matter?

74
00:05:59,892 --> 00:06:03,062
Could you check
the autopsy records of my parents?

75
00:06:05,431 --> 00:06:06,966
Your parents?

76
00:06:08,901 --> 00:06:12,071
They might have died
before the stabbings happened.

77
00:06:14,574 --> 00:06:15,775
Mr. Kagura.

78
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:19,045
I'm begging you.

79
00:06:20,279 --> 00:06:21,748
AUTOPSY REPORT
SAKUTARO TAGUSARI

80
00:06:28,121 --> 00:06:29,355
Indeed,

81
00:06:29,422 --> 00:06:32,492
the possibility that they were
already dead isn't zero.

82
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:34,861
For both of them,

83
00:06:34,927 --> 00:06:37,797
the vital reactions
from death are unclear.

84
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:40,733
If the bleeding occurred
shortly after death,

85
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:43,302
it may be due to blood remaining
in the veins and capillaries

86
00:06:43,369 --> 00:06:45,605
leaking out because of gravity.

87
00:06:47,306 --> 00:06:48,875
So they were already dead?

88
00:06:48,941 --> 00:06:50,610
I can't say for sure, though.

89
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:55,815
There were obvious stab wounds,
so they probably judged it a stabbing.

90
00:06:57,784 --> 00:07:00,453
If it wasn't a stabbing,
how did the real culprit do it?

91
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:02,422
Since an autopsy was performed,

92
00:07:02,488 --> 00:07:05,124
it doesn't leave
a lot of possibilities, but…

93
00:07:08,661 --> 00:07:09,562
Could it be…

94
00:07:28,815 --> 00:07:30,082
Amagi is dead.

95
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:32,118
What?

96
00:07:32,185 --> 00:07:33,586
Now, we have no choice

97
00:07:33,653 --> 00:07:36,589
but to look for Sasaoka,
and talk to Mr. Koike again.

98
00:07:39,592 --> 00:07:40,793
What about on your end?

99
00:07:42,595 --> 00:07:44,030
Our parents…

100
00:07:44,764 --> 00:07:46,666
It's possible they were poisoned.

101
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,634
Poisoned?

102
00:07:49,268 --> 00:07:50,803
Dr. Kagura said so.

103
00:07:51,604 --> 00:07:53,306
They tested for it back then, right?

104
00:07:53,372 --> 00:07:58,811
In 1995, the testing
was limited to major drugs and toxins.

105
00:07:58,878 --> 00:08:01,247
Only a few dozen types,

106
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:03,850
like cyanide or sleeping pills.

107
00:08:04,917 --> 00:08:07,453
It wouldn't be surprising
if they missed a poison.

108
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:10,056
Then, if they check the samples…

109
00:08:10,122 --> 00:08:12,792
It was 31 years ago.
They've already been disposed of.

110
00:08:14,393 --> 00:08:16,729
There's no way to investigate further.

111
00:08:21,734 --> 00:08:23,035
It's coming up soon.

112
00:08:26,105 --> 00:08:27,406
Dad's birthday.

113
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:32,245
I don't really remember them.

114
00:08:36,482 --> 00:08:38,017
They were the same every year.

115
00:08:40,319 --> 00:08:42,455
Even when we gave him letters or gifts,

116
00:08:43,422 --> 00:08:45,625
he would only give us a blunt response.

117
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:48,895
But…

118
00:08:50,897 --> 00:08:53,165
before going to bed,
he would drink alcohol,

119
00:08:53,232 --> 00:08:54,667
get tipsy,

120
00:08:55,635 --> 00:08:57,670
and reread the letters over and over,

121
00:08:59,438 --> 00:09:01,541
saying, "Getting older isn't so bad."

122
00:09:02,942 --> 00:09:04,443
And smiling happily.

123
00:09:10,850 --> 00:09:14,787
We're already older than our parents were.

124
00:09:16,122 --> 00:09:18,124
Dad was one year younger than me, huh.

125
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:29,669
It's delicious!

126
00:09:29,735 --> 00:09:31,237
You guys want to try some?

127
00:09:31,304 --> 00:09:32,572
<i>No!</i>

128
00:09:34,006 --> 00:09:36,075
I poured on too much.

129
00:09:36,676 --> 00:09:37,543
Yummy.

130
00:09:50,222 --> 00:09:51,824
It should be in here somewhere.

131
00:09:51,891 --> 00:09:52,858
You take that side.

132
00:10:23,255 --> 00:10:24,156
Found it.

133
00:10:30,429 --> 00:10:31,430
Makoto.

134
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:41,340
We're the only ones
who didn't have any that day.

135
00:10:41,407 --> 00:10:42,942
You're using that again?

136
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:45,011
It's delicious!

137
00:10:45,077 --> 00:10:46,846
You guys want to try some?

138
00:10:46,912 --> 00:10:48,214
No!

139
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:49,382
No!

140
00:10:50,383 --> 00:10:51,984
<i>If something had poison in it…</i>

141
00:10:52,051 --> 00:10:53,719
then it has to be this.

142
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:06,732
Dr. Kagura.

143
00:11:06,799 --> 00:11:08,534
The screening results are out.

144
00:11:08,601 --> 00:11:09,602
Thank you.

145
00:11:14,006 --> 00:11:16,542
TOXIN SCREENING RESULTS

146
00:11:19,845 --> 00:11:21,981
NO POSITIVES

147
00:11:22,048 --> 00:11:24,283
As I thought, no toxins are showing up.

148
00:11:29,722 --> 00:11:32,058
Please try again with a different panel.

149
00:11:32,825 --> 00:11:36,896
That day, the only thing my parents had
that we didn't was this vinegar.

150
00:11:36,962 --> 00:11:39,999
I heard you used to be colleagues
with Takahiro Sasaoka.

151
00:11:40,066 --> 00:11:41,200
Are you still in touch?

152
00:11:43,836 --> 00:11:45,705
I see, thank you very much.

153
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:47,440
I'm home.

154
00:11:47,506 --> 00:11:48,574
Any toxins?

155
00:11:48,641 --> 00:11:50,009
Nothing came up.

156
00:11:57,983 --> 00:11:59,118
Where are you going?

157
00:11:59,618 --> 00:12:00,453
Germany.

158
00:12:00,519 --> 00:12:01,487
What?

159
00:12:01,987 --> 00:12:03,355
I asked Dr. Kagura

160
00:12:03,422 --> 00:12:06,592
to write me a letter of introduction
to a forensics lab over there.

161
00:12:06,659 --> 00:12:08,494
Using Japan's drug screenings,

162
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:12,431
only 200 types of compounds
can be checked at a time.

163
00:12:12,498 --> 00:12:13,499
What about Germany?

164
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:16,969
A single analysis can handle
16,000 substances.

165
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:19,038
It's that big a difference?

166
00:12:22,274 --> 00:12:23,509
If a poison is found,

167
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:26,378
it means the killer isn't Mogi.

168
00:12:28,214 --> 00:12:30,015
I'll definitely find it.

169
00:12:48,901 --> 00:12:52,738
MAKOTO TAGUSARI
CAN'T YOU FIND ANY LEADS ON SASAOKA?

170
00:12:55,307 --> 00:13:01,647
NOTICE OF CLOSURE

171
00:13:01,714 --> 00:13:03,816
BANK BALANCE

172
00:13:03,883 --> 00:13:06,285
DEPOSIT

173
00:13:08,187 --> 00:13:10,556
I'm a pathetic older brother, aren't I?

174
00:13:12,391 --> 00:13:14,293
This is all I could leave for him.

175
00:13:18,130 --> 00:13:21,400
BANKBOOK
MINORU TAGUSARI

176
00:13:29,508 --> 00:13:31,477
<i>I don't want to be alone.</i>

177
00:13:32,711 --> 00:13:34,380
Please spare me from that at least.

178
00:13:49,328 --> 00:13:51,330
-What's the rate?
-One point equals one yen.

179
00:13:53,199 --> 00:13:55,334
A man named Sasaoka came here, right?

180
00:13:55,901 --> 00:13:58,571
Don't know. Tons of people come here.

181
00:14:00,573 --> 00:14:02,141
Where is Sasaoka?

182
00:14:03,475 --> 00:14:05,678
I told you, I really don't know.

183
00:14:23,729 --> 00:14:25,931
When are you coming back?

184
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:30,336
If you're just slacking off in a place
like this, please get back to work.

185
00:14:31,237 --> 00:14:32,738
What about you?

186
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:35,040
Today is my day off.

187
00:14:40,446 --> 00:14:41,413
Kudo.

188
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:44,917
I won't come back.

189
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:50,589
I went to see a lawyer.

190
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:55,227
They introduced me to the family of a
murder victim where the statute expired.

191
00:14:57,062 --> 00:14:59,365
The family said that no matter
how many years pass,

192
00:14:59,431 --> 00:15:01,667
the hatred toward the culprit
doesn't change.

193
00:15:03,102 --> 00:15:05,004
But they said they forgave them.

194
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:12,645
Because if they kept going,
even their own lives would be ruined.

195
00:15:13,445 --> 00:15:16,015
They didn't want the culprit
to steal anything more from them.

196
00:15:16,715 --> 00:15:18,851
So they decided to move forward.

197
00:15:28,227 --> 00:15:30,829
I was stuck in place too.

198
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:35,768
That's why,

199
00:15:38,804 --> 00:15:40,205
I intend to accept

200
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:43,175
my mother.

201
00:15:47,713 --> 00:15:49,081
So Tagusari, your revenge--

202
00:15:49,148 --> 00:15:50,549
I'm sorry, Kudo.

203
00:15:56,689 --> 00:16:00,492
Looks like I won't be able
to keep our promise to go for drinks.

204
00:16:16,108 --> 00:16:17,509
What happened to Sakutaro?

205
00:16:19,445 --> 00:16:21,280
He's not coming today.

206
00:16:21,347 --> 00:16:22,581
I see.

207
00:16:23,148 --> 00:16:25,985
I wonder when Makoto and Minoru will come?

208
00:16:30,356 --> 00:16:32,157
It would be nice if they came.

209
00:16:49,141 --> 00:16:51,176
-Another glass, please.
-Certainly.

210
00:16:51,243 --> 00:16:53,212
I looked into them for you.

211
00:16:53,779 --> 00:16:55,214
Sorry, I know you're busy.

212
00:16:59,551 --> 00:17:01,086
Here is what I have on him.

213
00:17:02,554 --> 00:17:04,390
Can I get the grilled meat set?

214
00:17:06,291 --> 00:17:07,493
Get the special one.

215
00:17:08,861 --> 00:17:10,262
-Thank you.
-Here you go.

216
00:17:10,329 --> 00:17:12,331
One grilled meat set, make it a special.

217
00:17:12,398 --> 00:17:14,299
-Certainly.
-Thanks.

218
00:17:17,069 --> 00:17:19,204
Did something happen with that fisherman?

219
00:17:19,938 --> 00:17:21,106
Kind of.

220
00:17:47,332 --> 00:17:49,201
Please hand this to the chief.

221
00:17:50,002 --> 00:17:50,836
What?

222
00:17:53,305 --> 00:17:54,306
Also,

223
00:17:55,140 --> 00:17:56,942
go grab a meal with Kudo for me.

224
00:17:58,377 --> 00:17:59,211
Um…

225
00:18:03,715 --> 00:18:05,651
Hey, Mr. Tagusari.

226
00:18:07,553 --> 00:18:08,954
Why are you doing this?

227
00:18:11,390 --> 00:18:12,391
PORK STEAK SET

228
00:19:24,163 --> 00:19:25,197
<i>Hello, Makoto?</i>

229
00:19:25,697 --> 00:19:27,266
<i>They found the poison.</i>

230
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:30,936
A powder derived from
a poisonous plant called digitalis.

231
00:19:36,108 --> 00:19:37,242
<i>Hello?</i>

232
00:19:38,544 --> 00:19:41,446
Then, it's just as Fumi said.

233
00:19:41,947 --> 00:19:43,615
Mogi isn't the killer.

234
00:19:44,349 --> 00:19:46,485
Someone put poison in that bottle.

235
00:19:54,693 --> 00:19:56,361
I want to look into something.

236
00:19:58,664 --> 00:19:59,998
Help me out.

237
00:20:00,065 --> 00:20:04,970
YOMOGIDA POLICE STATION

238
00:20:14,046 --> 00:20:16,448
ADMINISTRATION DEPARTMENT

239
00:20:23,188 --> 00:20:24,990
I'm Tagusari, from the Aoi Station.

240
00:20:27,826 --> 00:20:30,095
Examiner Tagusari from HQ
told us about you.

241
00:20:30,162 --> 00:20:31,163
This way, please.

242
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:38,003
TAKAHIRO SASAOKA

243
00:20:44,376 --> 00:20:45,944
Koike here.

244
00:20:54,853 --> 00:20:56,021
Explain it to me.

245
00:20:56,588 --> 00:20:58,223
Why have those clothes examined?

246
00:21:10,969 --> 00:21:13,939
Two days after the gun deal
was called off…

247
00:21:15,807 --> 00:21:18,243
a fisherman drowned at Yomogida Port.

248
00:21:23,415 --> 00:21:24,383
Is this…

249
00:21:25,150 --> 00:21:26,985
The courier who was killed.

250
00:21:41,466 --> 00:21:44,036
And from the clothes
on the day of the incident…

251
00:21:46,238 --> 00:21:47,472
they found poison.

252
00:21:55,347 --> 00:21:56,882
We've found the killer.

253
00:22:01,553 --> 00:22:02,754
Why?

254
00:22:07,459 --> 00:22:08,694
Just why?

255
00:22:16,768 --> 00:22:19,371
We chased this for 31 years…

256
00:22:24,209 --> 00:22:25,410
Why?

257
00:23:00,245 --> 00:23:01,313
Where are you going?

258
00:23:02,013 --> 00:23:03,815
To submit my resignation letter.

259
00:23:04,649 --> 00:23:05,684
Right now?

260
00:23:06,284 --> 00:23:08,987
It would be bad
if an active officer committed a crime.

261
00:23:11,089 --> 00:23:12,157
I suppose so.

262
00:23:14,426 --> 00:23:16,461
I called them
to the Yomogida Port at seven.

263
00:23:17,129 --> 00:23:18,864
I'll be back by then.

264
00:23:25,837 --> 00:23:28,273
AOI STATION
SAY NO TO ROAD RAGE

265
00:23:34,613 --> 00:23:35,814
Mr. Sasaoka.

266
00:23:37,082 --> 00:23:39,084
Sorry, I'm late.

267
00:23:52,063 --> 00:23:55,600
That person
is Mr. Koike's former partner, right?

268
00:24:04,342 --> 00:24:05,944
<i>Back then,</i>

269
00:24:06,011 --> 00:24:10,515
I was aware of the collusion
between you and the Igarashi-gumi.

270
00:24:13,985 --> 00:24:14,953
But…

271
00:24:16,455 --> 00:24:18,190
I didn't do anything.

272
00:24:19,925 --> 00:24:22,227
I turned a blind eye.

273
00:24:24,196 --> 00:24:27,833
I heard you tried to resign back then.

274
00:24:29,801 --> 00:24:32,537
But the higher-ups didn't accept it.

275
00:24:35,574 --> 00:24:40,078
You were really good to me back then.

276
00:24:43,048 --> 00:24:45,450
I was weak.

277
00:24:54,192 --> 00:24:56,962
I am truly sorry.

278
00:25:12,310 --> 00:25:15,146
For soliciting Mogi to commit murder,

279
00:25:15,881 --> 00:25:19,417
you will be questioned
by the First Division.

280
00:25:28,260 --> 00:25:31,696
Why did Mr. Sasaoka confess now,
after all this time?

281
00:25:32,330 --> 00:25:33,732
The statute expired, right?

282
00:25:36,034 --> 00:25:39,137
The Tagusari case isn't over yet.

283
00:25:41,573 --> 00:25:43,275
Find him.

284
00:25:46,845 --> 00:25:48,914
Tagusari is in possession of a gun.

285
00:25:50,715 --> 00:25:52,517
We've been on patrol
for two days straight.

286
00:25:52,584 --> 00:25:53,718
That's true.

287
00:27:02,854 --> 00:27:03,922
Makoto.

288
00:27:08,460 --> 00:27:10,729
You actually called them
out here sooner, right?

289
00:27:13,231 --> 00:27:14,399
Did I get found out?

290
00:27:18,103 --> 00:27:19,838
You're terrible at lying.

291
00:27:22,040 --> 00:27:23,375
Just like Dad.

292
00:27:32,817 --> 00:27:34,786
I'm glad you're my brother, Makoto.

293
00:27:42,327 --> 00:27:43,328
What?

294
00:27:49,567 --> 00:27:50,702
Nothing.

295
00:27:56,841 --> 00:27:58,109
Hand over the gun.

296
00:28:30,408 --> 00:28:31,576
Ms. Kudo.

297
00:28:33,478 --> 00:28:34,713
He's nowhere to be found.

298
00:28:34,779 --> 00:28:36,281
He didn't return home either.

299
00:28:38,149 --> 00:28:39,584
Where could Mr. Tagusari be?

300
00:28:40,285 --> 00:28:41,920
Shouldn't we report this to the chief?

301
00:28:42,487 --> 00:28:43,655
If we do that…

302
00:28:43,722 --> 00:28:47,358
Are you going to just let him
become a murderer?

303
00:28:53,264 --> 00:28:54,833
<i>Kudo speaking.</i>

304
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:58,770
I heard the younger Tagusari
was in Yomogida today.

305
00:28:59,637 --> 00:29:01,840
Apparently, he was walking toward the sea.

306
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:04,642
<i>Kudo, take Ishizaka and head there.</i>

307
00:29:04,709 --> 00:29:05,910
Understood.

308
00:29:05,977 --> 00:29:08,980
It's the police's fault that the case
wasn't investigated properly.

309
00:29:09,514 --> 00:29:10,482
This time,

310
00:29:10,982 --> 00:29:13,017
<i>I want to protect those brothers.</i>

311
00:29:13,518 --> 00:29:15,553
The courier fisherman who was killed…

312
00:29:19,624 --> 00:29:21,059
<i>was Koji Ashikaga.</i>

313
00:29:21,126 --> 00:29:22,794
AUTOPSY RESULTS

314
00:29:23,561 --> 00:29:24,629
Your father, right?

315
00:29:34,372 --> 00:29:39,878
1995, APRIL 15

316
00:29:44,115 --> 00:29:45,283
-Excuse me.
-What happened?

317
00:29:45,350 --> 00:29:47,152
-Please stop, miss.
-Koji…

318
00:29:47,218 --> 00:29:49,687
He got drunk and fell into the sea!

319
00:29:53,958 --> 00:29:55,994
Sorry, I know you're going through a lot.

320
00:29:56,060 --> 00:29:57,629
YOMOGIDA FISHING ASSOCIATION

321
00:29:57,695 --> 00:30:01,032
This is your father's.
The union was keeping it.

322
00:30:07,138 --> 00:30:11,142
WORK NOTES

323
00:30:11,209 --> 00:30:14,412
KOJI ASHIKAGA

324
00:30:19,517 --> 00:30:21,252
AMAGI CALLED

325
00:30:21,319 --> 00:30:24,689
<i>"April 9th, Amagi called.</i>

326
00:30:24,756 --> 00:30:27,125
<i>The time and date of the deal</i>
<i>have been decided."</i>

327
00:30:29,961 --> 00:30:31,963
NO CARGO

328
00:30:32,030 --> 00:30:35,466
<i>"April 13th, the cargo didn't show up.</i>

329
00:30:36,467 --> 00:30:38,036
<i>The deal was called off.</i>

330
00:30:38,536 --> 00:30:41,172
<i>Did something happen</i>
<i>at the Karashima factory?"</i>

331
00:30:41,239 --> 00:30:42,640
KARASHIMA METAL FACTORY

332
00:30:43,341 --> 00:30:45,777
Do you know about that fisherman
who died at sea?

333
00:30:46,845 --> 00:30:47,879
Fisherman?

334
00:30:48,746 --> 00:30:51,149
He wasn't drunk or anything.

335
00:30:51,816 --> 00:30:53,051
He was murdered.

336
00:30:54,619 --> 00:30:56,387
Hold on a minute.

337
00:30:56,454 --> 00:31:00,058
He died because you brought that gun home.

338
00:31:03,962 --> 00:31:06,831
-Here, your <i>ankake</i>.
-Thanks.

339
00:31:06,898 --> 00:31:08,533
1995, APRIL 19

340
00:31:10,134 --> 00:31:11,569
-Hey!
-Yes?

341
00:31:11,636 --> 00:31:12,971
That's too much sauce!

342
00:31:13,037 --> 00:31:14,672
We always use this much at home.

343
00:31:14,739 --> 00:31:17,976
-Always?
-I'm telling you, it's really good.

344
00:31:19,344 --> 00:31:21,079
Yum!

345
00:31:22,380 --> 00:31:23,414
You know, we…

346
00:31:23,481 --> 00:31:24,482
<i>And then,</i>

347
00:31:25,450 --> 00:31:31,189
<i>I monitored your family's movements,</i>
<i>finding out where the spare key was hidden</i>

348
00:31:31,789 --> 00:31:33,658
<i>and when the house would be empty.</i>

349
00:31:35,627 --> 00:31:36,628
Haruko.

350
00:31:37,729 --> 00:31:39,831
Why don't you read these for a change?

351
00:31:51,109 --> 00:31:54,812
THE WHOLE PLANT IS HIGHLY TOXIC

352
00:32:22,707 --> 00:32:24,442
<i>Digitalis extracts</i>

353
00:32:25,109 --> 00:32:27,512
were found in our family's vinegar bottle.

354
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:32,150
If ingested, it can cause
the heart to stop functioning,

355
00:32:32,684 --> 00:32:34,085
leading to death.

356
00:32:36,721 --> 00:32:38,456
And from Haruko Ashikaga's clothes,

357
00:32:39,791 --> 00:32:42,460
<i>traces of digitalis were also found.</i>

358
00:32:42,527 --> 00:32:44,395
THE LONG-SLEEVED SHIRT'S RIGHT WRIST

359
00:32:44,462 --> 00:32:48,333
That day, Mogi rushed out of our house
and slashed a high school girl.

360
00:32:53,037 --> 00:32:54,072
Someone, help!

361
00:32:56,908 --> 00:32:58,576
Please, help me!

362
00:33:01,179 --> 00:33:02,146
It hurts!

363
00:33:02,213 --> 00:33:03,481
My parents…

364
00:33:03,548 --> 00:33:04,682
It hurts!

365
00:33:04,749 --> 00:33:07,185
I'll call an ambulance!
Where's your phone?

366
00:33:07,251 --> 00:33:09,654
It hurts… It hurts…

367
00:33:09,721 --> 00:33:10,688
Stay here.

368
00:33:10,755 --> 00:33:11,823
It hurts…

369
00:33:35,580 --> 00:33:37,548
I thought I had failed.

370
00:33:44,756 --> 00:33:46,024
I see.

371
00:33:50,828 --> 00:33:52,330
So it was really me.

372
00:33:56,167 --> 00:33:57,635
Why did you kill them?

373
00:34:01,406 --> 00:34:03,641
Just because they didn't deliver the guns?

374
00:34:06,344 --> 00:34:10,782
My father also just failed
to deliver the guns.

375
00:34:15,053 --> 00:34:16,788
My whole family died.

376
00:34:21,259 --> 00:34:23,261
My dear father…

377
00:34:27,799 --> 00:34:29,967
Why did you help us all this time?

378
00:34:36,140 --> 00:34:37,341
Haruko!

379
00:34:50,321 --> 00:34:52,256
Because you always call my name like that.

380
00:34:53,658 --> 00:34:54,826
"Haruko."

381
00:34:55,426 --> 00:34:56,561
"Haruko."

382
00:35:03,134 --> 00:35:04,869
<i>We went fishing together,</i>

383
00:35:07,004 --> 00:35:09,474
<i>put candles on fried rice to celebrate…</i>

384
00:35:15,913 --> 00:35:17,815
I even celebrated you finding a job…

385
00:35:23,921 --> 00:35:25,957
In you both,

386
00:35:28,626 --> 00:35:30,628
I saw my dead younger brother.

387
00:35:37,735 --> 00:35:40,471
But being with you became too painful.

388
00:35:42,073 --> 00:35:43,174
That's why,

389
00:35:44,108 --> 00:35:47,311
when the statute expired,
I ran away from you two.

390
00:35:51,649 --> 00:35:53,751
Then why did you come back?

391
00:35:55,052 --> 00:35:56,721
You were free, right?

392
00:36:04,662 --> 00:36:06,797
But the guilt never went away.

393
00:36:10,434 --> 00:36:11,736
No matter where I was,

394
00:36:13,971 --> 00:36:15,840
no matter how much I smiled…

395
00:36:19,544 --> 00:36:24,615
Every night, before I slept,
your faces would flash before my eyes.

396
00:36:35,927 --> 00:36:39,797
I've decided to finally…

397
00:36:46,904 --> 00:36:48,673
surrender myself to my fate.

398
00:36:53,844 --> 00:36:55,313
That's why I'm here.

399
00:37:10,728 --> 00:37:12,830
Your revenge was successful.

400
00:37:20,504 --> 00:37:21,906
How does it feel?

401
00:37:27,378 --> 00:37:28,946
I think…

402
00:37:31,048 --> 00:37:34,252
I wanted to be judged by you two.

403
00:38:25,303 --> 00:38:26,971
I'll handle the rest.

404
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:41,085
Because that's the only way

405
00:38:42,620 --> 00:38:44,155
you two would forgive me.

406
00:40:17,548 --> 00:40:18,849
Hey, Minoru.

407
00:40:23,287 --> 00:40:25,556
What do you want to be when you grow up?

408
00:40:33,697 --> 00:40:34,865
I'm already grown.

409
00:40:39,937 --> 00:40:41,505
What do you want to be?

410
00:40:58,956 --> 00:40:59,990
A ninja.

411
00:41:09,066 --> 00:41:10,334
What about you, Makoto?

412
00:41:17,508 --> 00:41:18,809
I…

413
00:41:24,448 --> 00:41:25,983
I wonder.

414
00:41:47,004 --> 00:41:48,672
This is the end of the line.

415
00:41:54,345 --> 00:42:00,317
YOMOGIDA POLICE STATION

416
00:42:18,736 --> 00:42:20,004
Alright!

417
00:42:20,070 --> 00:42:22,406
Well then, let's eat!

418
00:42:22,473 --> 00:42:24,542
-Let's eat.
-Let's eat.

419
00:42:29,013 --> 00:42:30,548
Hey, come on! What're you doing?

420
00:42:30,614 --> 00:42:32,883
Come on, just try it.
You can blame me later.

421
00:42:32,950 --> 00:42:34,985
-It's delicious!
-No!

422
00:42:35,052 --> 00:42:36,820
-Please don't!
-Come on, it's good.

423
00:42:36,887 --> 00:42:39,290
-Let me put it on for you!
-Thank you.

424
00:42:39,356 --> 00:42:41,592
Okay, let’s eat!

425
00:42:41,659 --> 00:42:43,127
-Thanks for the meal.
-Yes.

426
00:42:50,267 --> 00:42:51,502
Yummy!

427
00:42:51,569 --> 00:42:53,737
-Well?
-It's good.

428
00:42:53,804 --> 00:42:55,072
See.

429
00:42:55,706 --> 00:42:56,707
It's so sour.

430
00:43:44,355 --> 00:43:45,623
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.
